overview: The user initiated the project by providing a Statement of Work for a
  sleep questionnaire application, seeking to add database capabilities, an
  admin dashboard, and authentication. The plan involved updating the
  demographics fields in the questionnaire, creating a Prisma model for
   to store data, and developing API endpoints for
  saving, retrieving, and exporting responses as CSV. A key decision was to
  implement a simple password-based authentication system for the admin
  dashboard. Initially, a custom session management was built, but it was later
  refined to leverage Next.js middleware for more streamlined route protection.
  The implementation included creating login/logout API routes and dedicated
  admin dashboard pages. Comprehensive testing confirmed that all database
  operations, API endpoints, and the authentication system were fully
  functional, ensuring a robust backend for the application.
